TITLE OF RESEARCH: Profile Bias in Social Media User Content Moderation

PRINCIPAL INVESTIGATOR: Jay Li

PRINCIPAL INVESTIGATOR’S DEPARTMENT: Computer Science



Key information about the study:

Your informed consent is being sought for research. Participation in the research is voluntary.



The purpose of the research: Investigate if content reviewers exhibit bias in moderating the flagged social media activities, and if they do, whether this bias is related to specific characteristics of a flagged user’s profile, such as their gender, race, ethnicity, geographic location, or income level. 



The expected duration of the subject's participation: 5-10 minutes.  



The procedures that the subject will be asked to follow in the research: Complete the survey on rating Facebook posts.



The benefits to the subject or to others, e.g., society that may reasonably be expected from the research: In social media moderation, if bias exists, then it is important to evaluate it quantitatively especially in the future when social media platforms will be utilizing machine learning to develop autonomous programs that will determine what is or is not appropriate on their platforms. It will be crucial to prevent such intelligent systems from developing bias of their own.



The reasonably foreseeable risks or discomforts to the subject as a result of participation: The subject will be exposed to content that could potentially be offensive and make them feel uncomfortable. 



Additional information about the study:

Confidentiality: All records from this study will be kept confidential. Your responses will be kept private, and we will not include any information that will make it possible to identify you in any report we might publish. The research team will be the only party that will have access to your data.



Compensation: Participants will be compensated $5.
